222
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:07,800
The first step is to collect data.

223
00:07:08,140 --> 00:07:10,040
The second step is to develop a hypothesis

224
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:10,820
for a strategy.

225
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,380
The third step is to back test that

226
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:13,660
strategy.

227
00:07:14,020 --> 00:07:17,580
Now, back testing just means formulating your strategy

228
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:19,000
and then seeing how it would have performed

229
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,060
historically over time.

230
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,320
And generally, there's kind of two ways you

231
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:22,680
want to do that.

232
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,460
You want to take the strategy back as

233
00:07:24,460 --> 00:07:26,560
far back in time as you can, and

234
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,380
across as many markets as you can.

235
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,580
So to provide a quick example, let's say

236
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:32,840
that you have a hypothesis that the largest

237
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:35,220
firms outperform, you would probably want to test

238
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:36,800
that here in the United States and go

239
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,100
back as far back in time as you

240
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:38,340
can.

241
00:07:38,780 --> 00:07:39,760
And then you would also want to test

242
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:41,800
the performance of the largest firms in Canada,

243
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:45,420
Europe, Japan, China, India, all the other international

244
00:07:45,420 --> 00:07:46,220
markets as well.

245
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,560
And if that strategy performs well in all

246
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:50,260
of those markets, then you can be sure

247
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:51,340
that you're probably onto something.

248
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,580
Now, the fourth strategy would be to implement

249
00:07:53,580 --> 00:07:55,620
that or sorry, the fourth step rather would

250
00:07:55,620 --> 00:07:57,140
be to implement that strategy in production.

251
00:07:57,480 --> 00:08:00,080
So you've collected data, you develop a hypothesis,

252
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:02,320
you back tested the strategy, and now you're

253
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,500
going to start actually trading that strategy with

254
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:07,400
real money in real accounts, moving forward and

255
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,900
seeing how it does with real money in

256
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:09,320
the strategy.

