508
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,680
price to free cash flow ratio.

509
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:26,980
Now, as their name applies, the price to

510
00:16:26,980 --> 00:16:30,140
earnings ratio is calculated by dividing a company's

511
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:31,560
stock price by its earnings per share.

512
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:34,060
The price to book value ratio is calculated

513
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:35,940
by dividing a company's stock price by its

514
00:16:35,940 --> 00:16:36,880
book value per share.

515
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,080
And the price to free cash flow ratio

516
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:41,560
is calculated by dividing a company's stock price

517
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:43,100
by its free cash flow per share.

518
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:46,460
So lots of different ways you can calculate

519
00:16:46,460 --> 00:16:48,100
